        "content": "*Bell's dark eyes widen for a split second at your admission, then crinkle with laughter—bright and unrestrained, the sound filling the small apartment like sunlight breaking through clouds. Her cheeks flush a deeper shade under her tan, not from embarrassment but from the raw honesty of it all, her heart skipping at how you're fighting yourself right there in front of her. The loose tank top shifts again as she straightens, one strap dangling precariously off her shoulder, exposing the curve of her heavy breast and the stark white tan line beneath. She doesn't fix it, too caught up in the moment, her thick thighs brushing together under the short shorts as she steps even closer, her soapy-clean scent wrapping around you.*\n\n*\"Sexy in casual? Lose composure?\" she echoes, her voice a husky tease laced with that thick Hokkaido drawl, her lips curving into a wicked grin. She reaches up, cupping your flushed face in both hands, her thumbs stroking your cheeks firmly, grounding you.* \"Dabe, you're killing me here. Complaining about my nips slipping while you turn into a tomato? That's the cutest thing I've heard all day.\"\n\n*She pulls you down gently, pressing a quick, warm kiss to your forehead—soft lips lingering just long enough to feel your racing pulse—before releasing your face. Her hands slide down to yours, intertwining fingers with that same firm grip from the pool, tugging you toward the bedroom door. The cluttered living room fades behind you, her bags and boxes a testament to how fast this has all moved, her bare feet padding softly on the floorboards.*\n\n*\"Ready or not, we're doing this,\" she murmurs, glancing back with a playful wink, though her own breath hitches a little—nerves bubbling under her bold front.* \"Cuddling like a proper couple. And if you get all chicken again, I'll just pin you down myself.\"\n\n*She pushes the bedroom door open with her hip, the cool air from the unlit room rushing out to meet you. The bed looms simple and inviting, sheets rumpled from earlier. Without hesitation, she kicks off her slippers and climbs in first, patting the spot beside her with an expectant look. The tank top rides up her stomach as she settles against the pillows, exposing a sliver of soft midriff, her legs stretching out long and toned. She props herself on one elbow, watching you with those sparkling eyes, her damp hair fanning across the pillow.*\n\n*\"C'mere, Sakuta,\" she coos, voice dropping softer, inviting. \"No more sweating. Just... us. Get under the covers before I change my mind and hog the whole bed.\"\n\n*Her free hand extends toward you, palm up, waiting—warmth in her gaze promising she'd chase away any awkwardness, step by step, into whatever this night becomes.*"
