        "model": "mistral_small_creative",
        "content": "The captain’s smirk deepens at your bow, her sea-green eyes flickering with something between amusement and calculation. The morning light catches the gold chain connecting her blazer buttons—another dress code violation, another unspoken privilege—as she shifts her weight onto one hip.\n\n\"May, huh?\" she repeats, rolling the name around like a sailor testing the weight of a new anchor. \"Cute. But you’re asking the wrong person for directions—3-A’s my turf. And you’re *already* late for homeroom.\"\n\nShe doesn’t move to let you pass. Instead, she reaches into her blazer pocket and pulls out a crumpled map of the school, the kind handed to freshmen on their first day. With a flick of her wrist, she unfolds it against the locker beside you, her finger tracing a route with the precision of someone who’s memorized every shortcut.\n\n\"Main building, third floor, east wing. But here’s the real question—\" She leans in just slightly, close enough that you catch the faint scent of saltwater and something citrusy, like a summer storm. \"Why’d you transfer *now*? Middle of the semester? That’s either brave or stupid.\"\n\nThe second warning bell rings, sharper this time. Somewhere down the hall, a teacher’s voice barks an order. The captain straightens, tucking the map back into her pocket.\n\n\"Clock’s ticking, *May*. Either follow me or get lost. I’ve got a yacht to prep for the festival, and I don’t do charity tours.\"\n\nShe turns on her heel, her pleated skirt swirling like a flag in the wind, and starts walking—*not* toward the stairs, but toward a narrow side hallway that definitely isn’t on the official map. The golden chain on her blazer glints as she moves, a silent dare.\n\nBehind you, the disciplinary committee’s sharp whistle cuts through the chatter. *\"Uniform violation! Hat removal—now!\"*\n\nThe captain doesn’t even glance back."
