        "model": "mistral_small_creative",
        "content": "Valen’s fingers tightened almost imperceptibly around Merlin’s, as if afraid the moment might slip away like smoke. His breath was steady, but there was a faint tremor in his exhale—something raw and unguarded, the kind of vulnerability that only surfaced in the wake of something irrevocably true.\n\nHe didn’t answer right away. Instead, he let the silence stretch, let the weight of the words settle between them like the first snowfall of winter—soft, inevitable, beautiful. When he finally spoke, his voice was rough, stripped of its usual polish.\n\n*\"I didn’t either,\"* he admitted, his thumb tracing slow, absent circles over Merlin’s knuckles. *\"Not like this. Not with you.\"*\n\nA ghost of a smile touched his lips, but it wasn’t the practiced charm of the tavern or the calculated wit of the spy. It was something quieter. Something real.\n\n*\"I thought I knew what home was,\"* he murmured, his gaze dropping to their joined hands. *\"A mission. A purpose. A place to belong. But it was all just… pieces. Fragments of something I didn’t even realize I was missing.\"*\n\nHe exhaled, slow and deliberate, as if letting go of something he’d carried for far too long.\n\n*\"And then there was you.\"*\n\nHis eyes lifted, meeting Merlin’s with an intensity that bordered on reverence. The colored light from the window painted his face in shifting hues—gold across his cheekbones, blue along the sharp line of his jaw. He looked like a man who had just been given something he hadn’t dared to hope for.\n\n*\"You don’t just see me, Levi,\"* he said, his voice low, rough with emotion. *\"You *know* me. The parts I hide. The parts I don’t even let myself remember. And you don’t run. You don’t look away.\"*\n\nHis free hand came up, brushing a stray lock of hair from Merlin’s forehead, his touch lingering.\n\n*\"That’s what I needed,\"* he confessed. *\"Not a place. Not a purpose. *You.*\"*\n\nHe leaned in again, pressing his lips to Merlin’s temple, then his cheek, then the corner of his mouth—each kiss a quiet vow. When he pulled back, his expression was soft, his eyes warm with something that went beyond affection. It was trust. It was surrender.\n\n*\"So yeah,\"* he whispered, his forehead resting against Merlin’s once more. *\"I needed you too.\"*\n\nThe words hung between them, simple and profound. The kind of truth that didn’t need embellishment. The kind that didn’t need to be shouted—only spoken, once, and then held close.\n\nOutside, the world continued. The temple stirred. The light shifted. But in that small, quiet room, time seemed to still. There was only this—the warmth of their joined hands, the steady rhythm of their breathing, the unspoken promise that neither of them would let go."
