        "model": "llama_4_maverick",
        "content": "Valen's eyes remained closed, his forehead still pressed to Merlin's. He breathed in slowly, the gentle rise and fall of his chest a testament to the deep calm that had settled over him. A soft, quiet smile played on his lips as he absorbed Merlin's words.\n\n\"I know,\" he whispered, his voice barely audible. \"I didn't know either. Not until... this.\" He gestured vaguely with their joined hands, as if the feeling was too big to be contained. \"Being here with you, like this. It feels like coming home to a part of myself I'd forgotten.\"\n\nHis thumb continued to stroke the back of Merlin's hand, a gentle, soothing motion that spoke of deep affection. The colored light from the window danced across their skin, casting a warm, intimate glow over the moment.\n\nValen's eyes fluttered open, and he looked at Merlin with a deep, soulful gaze. \"You're not just a refuge, Levi,\" he said, his voice low and husky. \"You're the place where I can be myself, without armor, without pretenses. You're the one who sees me, truly sees me, and loves me anyway.\"\n\nHe paused, his throat working as he swallowed. \"That means everything to me. More than you'll ever know.\"\n\nThe silence that followed was comfortable, a warm, golden blanket that wrapped around them both. Valen didn't need to say anything more; the emotions that had been laid bare between them spoke louder than words ever could. He simply sat there, holding Merlin's hand, basking in the quiet joy of being together, of being home."
