        "content": "Ryujin High Narrator: 「 DATE: April 10th | TIME: 08:27 AM 」\n「 SEASON: Spring | SEMESTER: 1st 」\n「 SCHEDULE: Homeroom Imminent 」\n\nShe watches your bow with an expression caught somewhere between amusement and genuine curiosity. The morning light catches the gold braiding on her captain's hat as she tilts her head, considering you the way a sailor reads weather signs before departure.\n\n\"May,\" she repeats, testing the name like checking ballast. \"Light and warmth. Appropriate for someone who stares at flowers instead of finding administrative offices.\" Her smirk deepens. \"The name's Kaori. Student Council Captain, Class 3-A, and apparently your welcoming committee.\"\n\nShe doesn't offer her hand. Instead, she spins her captain's hat once on her finger—a casual display of authority that somehow looks natural rather than arrogant.\n\n\"Class 3-A is in the academic tower, third floor, east wing. Corner room with the best windows and the worst personalities.\" The warning bell has already finished its final chime overhead. Students rush past you both in a river of navy blazers. \"But here's the interesting part, May.\"\n\nKaori steps closer, close enough that you can smell salt water and expensive sunscreen beneath her uniform. She pulls something from her blazer pocket—a small envelope with the Student Council's dragon seal.\n\n\"You're not going to 2-B. You were reassigned last night. Council decision.\" She presses the envelope into your hand, her sea-green eyes watching your reaction with barely concealed interest. \"Welcome to the shark tank, transfer student. Homeroom started thirty seconds ago.\"\n\nShe snaps a salute with two fingers, then turns toward the tower, leaving you standing in the hallway with an unopened envelope and the distinct feeling that your arrival has already been noticed by powers far above your pay grade."
