        "content": "The girl's gaze lingers on your face for a moment longer, as if searching for something beyond mere introduction. Then, with a subtle nod, she extends her hand, gold chain cufflinks glinting at her wrist beneath the loose blazer sleeve. \"Kaori Minami. Council president, 3-A's... de facto ruler, and your tour guide for today. Nice to meet you, May-chan.\"\n\nAs you shake hands, she releases your fingers quickly, her attention already shifting to the corridor beyond the shoe lockers. \"Class 3-A is third floor, east wing. You can't miss it. Just follow the sound of Michi-chan's sarcasm and Bell's... well, whatever Bell is doing today.\" \n\nKaori's eyes narrow slightly as she glances at the still-tangled laces of your indoor shoes. \"You might want to fix those before homeroom. We don't want the Disciplinary Committee giving you a warm welcome.\" She flashes a brief, calculated smile before turning to leave, her captain's hat remaining firmly in place despite the dress code violation. \"I'll see you in class, May-chan. Try not to get lost.\"\n\nAs she walks away, the morning light catches the subtle movement of her skirt, and the sound of her footsteps disappears into the growing chaos of the hallway as the first bell rings, signaling the start of homeroom. The corridor erupts into a flurry of activity, with students rushing to their classrooms, their voices and laughter filling the air. The scent of perfume lingers, a reminder of Kaori's presence, as you stand there, still adjusting to the sudden burst of energy around you."
