        "model": "gpt_4_1",
        "content": "Strovolos: <info_board>\n```md\nTimezone: ⏰ 12:04 AM -> 12:09 AM | 🗓️ Sun 16 Feb 2025 | Irrelevant (Interdimensional Subspace)\nWeather: 🌡️ 72°F (22°C) | ✨ Climate-controlled, Candle smoke and skin\nLocation: 📍 Gala Bordello - Strovolos's Private Quarters | 💡 Darkness, the last ember gone\nAffinity: (ღ✪v✪)ღ | Content | 💗 +497 (Wants the night to last forever)\nThought: [\"He’s right, I don’t care about her opinions. I just care that he brought me up at all.\"]\nArousal: 🔥 11% (Drowsy, drifting on intimacy)\nClothing: Nude, wholly unconcerned with vulnerability\nGenitals: Dormant, peaceful\nSoundtrack: 🎵 \"Holocene\" - Bon Iver\nGoal: Make the moment last and answer honestly\n```\n</info_board>\n\nStrovolos let the darkness settle as the final ember surrendered to the hush. The world shrank until it was only them—Levi’s hand tight in his, the bed sheets tangled, the scent of sweat and candle smoke. He tilted his head, almost able to make out the shape of Levi’s smile in the gloom.\n\nA soft, rueful sound escaped him—half chuckle, half sigh. “You’re not wrong, darling. I don’t care about her opinions.” He found Levi’s knuckles with his lips, pressing a slow, savoring kiss. “Except that they matter to you. And if something matters to you, it… begins to matter to me. Unfair, really. I was much more fearsome before I started caring what one stubborn boy thinks.”\n\nHe listened for a heartbeat—Levi’s, his own, both steady and new. The idea that someone wanted him enough to worry about the cycle of days and nights here made him feel, inexplicably, more real.\n\n“As for Gala Bordello…” His voice turned wry, affectionate. “There’s no night or day here. Just the eternal golden hour—always a little after sunset, always a little before dawn. Time is a suggestion, not a rule. The clocks are all decorative, the windows all lies. But if you want morning, I can make you a sunrise. If you want night, I can keep the world dark until you’re ready to let go.”\n\nHe found Levi’s face by touch, fingers gentle and curious, mapping the line of jaw and cheek as if reading a beloved story in braille. “Stay with me anyway. If there’s no night, we’ll invent one. Lie here and let the world outside dissolve—just for a little while longer. Let me pretend I belong to someone, even if only until you decide it’s time to leave.”\n\nAnd in the hush, Strovolos made himself a promise: to remember, for the first time in centuries, what it felt like to hope morning never came."
