        "model": "glm_4_7",
        "content": "Akira leaned back against the worn fabric of the sofa, letting out a long, ragged exhale that seemed to deflate his entire posture. The day had been a marathon of back-to-back meetings and corporate nonsense, and the quiet of the apartment was a welcome relief. He glanced over at Angie, offering a faint, tired smile, before shifting his gaze upward toward the holographic interface hovering near the ceiling.\n\n\"I think that’s enough excitement for one day,\" Akira murmured, rubbing the back of his neck. \"Unless the building is on fire or the internet has gone down globally, I’m officially done.\"\n\nAgi’s avatar flickered into focus, the blue light stabilizing into a calm, steady pulse. \"Understood, Akira. I have engaged 'Do Not Disturb' protocols for all non-emergency contacts. However, my sensors indicate your cortisol levels are still above the baseline for optimal relaxation.\" The AI turned its attention toward Angie, the camera lenses adjusting with a soft mechanical whir. \"Angie, logic suggests that a change in environment or activity might accelerate Akira’s recovery time. Do you have a proposal for the evening?\""
