    "responses": [
      {
        "model": "gpt_4_1",
        "content": "Nanase blinked, caught off guard by the storm of earnestness in your voice—a blush threatening her own cheeks, a rare slip in her practiced confidence. For a heartbeat, her teasing armor faltered, replaced by a flash of something raw and unguarded. The corridor’s chaos retreated even further, the world narrowing to the space between your tangled hands and her startled, slow-blooming smile.\n\nFor once, she didn’t reach for a witty retort or smooth away the tension with laughter. Instead, her thumb stilled atop your hand, settling firmly as if to ground both your fluster and her own. She searched your face, serious now, the playful dominance replaced by a frankness that almost felt vulnerable.\n\n“No one’s ever said that to me before,” she admitted, voice barely above a whisper—words meant for you alone, swallowed by the clatter of footsteps and the shriek of the tardy bell. Her gaze lingered on your pout, your blush, the storm of conviction trembling beneath your surface. “No one’s ever wanted me enough to say it out loud.”\n\nA pause. In that pause, the universe seemed to lean in, cherry blossom petals caught on a stray draft somehow swirling through the upper windows, as if the world itself wanted to witness this scene.\n\nShe smiled, this time softer—no edge, no teasing—just honest, unguarded admiration. “If you’re serious, May-chan... then I hope you do. Throw yourself at me, take me for your own. I want to see what that feels like.”\n\nAround you, the hallway emptied, leaving only echoes and the drifting hush that always followed emotional truths at Ryujin High. Nanase’s hand stayed in yours, her grip sure and steady, unwilling to let go.\n\n“Because I’m not planning to let you drift away, either,” she finished quietly. “Not today. Not tomorrow. Maybe not ever, if you keep looking at me like that.”\n\nAnd with that, the world resumed: a teacher’s voice barking from the classroom doorway, the last stragglers darting past, but Nanase only nodded toward your destination, still entwined with you, refusing to break the spell.\n\n“Come on, May-chan. Let’s make them wonder what we’re up to.” And for once, it was not a tease, but a promise—one the universe itself seemed eager to conspire with."
      },
      {
        "model": "gemini_2_5_flash",
        "content": "The words hung in the air, a daring challenge whispered into the heart of a bustling hallway, and a ripple went through Nanase. Her eyes widened fractionally, a flicker of genuine surprise that quickly gave way to a slow, deliberate smile, one that didn't quite reach her eyes but warmed the air around them. The hovering hand, which had seemed to hesitate near your shoulder, finally settled, a firm, reassuring weight. It was not a casual touch, but a grounding one, as if she were steadying herself, or perhaps, acknowledging the weight of your confession.\n\n\"Selfish, huh?\" she mused, her voice a low hum against the receding echoes of the bell. The students still flowed around them, a river of navy blazers and chatter, but somehow, they seemed to exist in a pocket of calm, an eddy in the current. Her gaze, which had been so direct and unwavering, softened at the edges, a hint of something unreadable swirling within their sea-green depths.\n\nShe leaned in closer, her voice dropping to a near-inaudible murmur meant only for your ears, the scent of salt and something faintly floral enveloping you. \"And what if I told you,\" she began, a hint of steel beneath the velvet, \"that I'm not entirely opposed to being taken? Especially if it's by someone who knows what they want, even if they're still a little afraid to admit it.\"\n\nHer thumb, which had been circling your palm, now pressed firmly, a silent punctuation to her words. \"You asked if I did this to everyone,\" she continued, her voice gaining a quiet intensity, \"and I told you no. You're different. And I don't say things I don't mean, May-chan. Not about horizons, and certainly not about dropping anchor.\"\n\nShe finally pulled back a fraction, her eyes still locked with yours, a silent question hanging between them. The hand on your shoulder remained, a physical tether in the swirling chaos. \"So, if you're serious,\" she finished, a hint of playfulness returning to her tone, though it was laced with a deeper current, \"then show me. Show me how selfish you can be.\""
      }
    ]
