        "content": "The hallway erupts into motion as the final bell’s echo fades—lockers slamming, shoes squeaking against polished floors, the distant thunder of students stampeding toward their classrooms. Yet for a single suspended moment, the world narrows to the sight of May’s retreating figure: a blur of navy and white, her half-tied shoelaces flapping like untamed sails as she bolts toward the stairs, her laughter trailing behind her like a wake.\n\nNanase watches, one corner of her mouth quirked upward, until the transfer student vanishes around the corner. Only then does she exhale, the sound carrying the faintest hint of amusement. *Drifting things indeed.*\n\nThe captain’s fingers tap against her thigh—*tap-tap*—a rhythm only she can hear. She turns toward the stairs herself, but not before her gaze flicks upward, toward the second-floor railing where a familiar silhouette leans against the banister, arms crossed.\n\nBell’s platinum hair glints under the fluorescent lights, her smirk sharp enough to cut glass. \"Well, well,\" she drawls, pushing off the railing with a deliberate sway of her hips. \"If it isn’t the *famous* Yacht Club Captain, playing tour guide for the new transfer. How… *uncharacteristically* kind of you.\"\n\nNanase doesn’t slow her stride, but her eyes narrow just slightly. \"Jealous, Bell? Or just bored enough to eavesdrop?\"\n\nBell’s laugh is a rich, throaty thing, the kind that carries. \"Oh, *please*. I was just admiring the view.\" She flicks a glance toward the stairs where May disappeared. \"She’s cute. A little *too* cute, if you ask me. All wide-eyed and flustered—like a baby seal that just washed up on shore.\"\n\nNanase’s steps falter for half a second. Just long enough for Bell to notice.\n\nThe gyaru’s grin turns predatory. \"Ohhh, so *that’s* how it is.\" She saunters down the stairs, falling into step beside Nanase with the ease of someone who’s done it a hundred times before. \"You’ve got that *look*, Captain. The one that says you’ve already decided she’s *yours* to keep an eye on.\"\n\nNanase side-eyes her. \"I don’t know what you’re talking about.\"\n\nBell snorts. \"Sure you don’t.\" She leans in, voice dropping to a conspiratorial whisper. \"But just so you know? Michi’s already got her claws out. And you *know* how she gets when someone new shows up and starts turning heads.\"\n\nA muscle twitches in Nanase’s jaw. The mention of Michi’s name is like a gust of wind shifting the sails—sudden, unavoidable. She doesn’t answer, but her fingers tap against her thigh again, faster this time.\n\nBell’s smirk softens, just for a second. \"Relax, Captain. I’m not gonna steal your little transfer.\" She nudges Nanase’s shoulder with her own, a rare moment of genuine camaraderie. \"But if you *do* decide to keep her, you might wanna warn her about Michi. And Kaori. And *definitely* Haru.\"\n\nNanase exhales through her nose, sharp and controlled. \"Noted.\"\n\nThey reach the landing, the noise of the hallway swallowing them whole. Bell lingers for a second, her expression unreadable. Then, with a wink, she peels off toward her own classroom, her voice floating back over her shoulder.\n\n\"Oh, and Captain? Try not to *drown* her on the first day.\"\n\nNanase watches her go, then turns toward the third floor, her steps deliberate. The weight of Bell’s words settles over her like the press of an incoming storm.\n\n*Third floor. Left past the gym.*\n\nShe knows the way.\n\nBut more importantly—she knows *who* will be waiting."
