        "content": "Valen’s eyes closed for a brief second as the words washed over him, a quiet absolution he hadn't known he was seeking. When he opened them again, the look he gave Merlin was stripped of every defense, every reflex to deflect or charm.\n\n\"I know,\" he whispered, his voice rough around the edges. \"I didn't know either. Until I found it.\"\n\nHe shifted then, just enough to wrap an arm around Merlin’s shoulders, pulling him into a loose, sideways embrace. It wasn't a hold born of desperation, but of simple, grounding necessity. He rested his chin against the top of Merlin’s head, inhaling the scent of him—clean skin, old stone, and the faint trace of magic that always clung to the mage like ozone.\n\n\"It's lonely,\" Valen murmured into the quiet, his lips moving against Merlin’s hair. \"Being the one who watches. The one who sees everything but isn't part of it. I thought... I thought I was used to it. That it was the price of the job.\"\n\nHe pulled back just enough to look down at Merlin, his hand moving to cup the back of Merlin’s neck, his thumb brushing the sensitive skin behind his ear. The colored light from the window had turned a soft, steady amber, filling the space between them with warmth.\n\n\"But you,\" he said, shaking his head slowly, a look of wonder breaking through the solemnity. \"You looked right through the mask. You didn't just see the spy or the soldier. You saw the man who just wanted...\" He trailed off, huffing a soft, self-deprecating laugh. \"I don't know. Eggs. Peace. A hand to hold.\"\n\nHe leaned forward, resting his forehead against Merlin’s once more, his voice dropping to a bare murmur.\n\n\"We have this now, Levi. Whatever happens outside that door... whatever mess the world throws at us next... we have this. And I'm not letting go.\"\n\nThe distant sound of footsteps echoed in the corridor outside, signaling the approach of the healer or perhaps just the temple staff beginning their rounds. Valen didn't flinch. He just tightened his grip on Merlin’s hand, anchoring them both in the golden light.\n\n\"Rest now,\" he said softly. \"I'll watch over you. I've got you.\""
