        "content": "The whiteboard’s chalk letters blur into abstract shapes as your mind spirals—*Nanase in a wedding dress, Nanase holding a tiny child with sea-green eyes, Nanase laughing as she chases you through cherry blossoms*—until the sharp *crack* of a ruler against wood snaps you back to reality.\n\n**\"Sakurajima.\"**\n\nThe teacher’s voice cuts through your daydream like a blade. The entire class turns to stare. Your face, already flushed, now feels like it’s been dipped in boiling water.\n\n**\"If you’re quite finished fantasizing about your future,\"** he says, deadpan, **\"perhaps you’d like to share your thoughts on the assigned reading?\"**\n\nA beat of silence. Then—\n\n**\"Oh, she’s *definitely* not reading,\"** Bell drawls from the front row, swiveling in her seat to smirk at you. **\"Look at her. She’s got that *I just saw a ghost* face. Or, y’know, a *really* pretty captain.\"**\n\nThe class erupts. Laughter, whispers, a few dramatic gasps. Someone in the back mimics your earlier bow, complete with a swooning hand to the forehead. You shrink into your seat, but the damage is done—your reputation as the *love-struck transfer student* is now officially cemented in Class 3-A’s collective memory.\n\nBehind you, Nanase exhales a quiet, amused breath. **\"You’re making this too easy, Sakurajima.\"**\n\nThe words are barely above a whisper, but they hit you like a physical touch. Your fingers twitch against your desk. The teacher clears his throat, clearly done with your antics.\n\n**\"Since you’re so *engaged*,\"** he says, **\"you can lead the discussion on *The Tale of Genji* next period. Alone.\"**\n\nA collective *oooh* rises from the class. Your stomach drops.\n\n**\"But—!\"**\n\n**\"No buts.\"** He taps his clipboard. **\"Unless you’d prefer to write a 5,000-word essay on the symbolism of cherry blossoms in classical literature instead?\"**\n\nYou swallow hard. **\"I—I’ll take the discussion.\"**\n\n**\"Good choice.\"** He turns back to the board, dismissing you with a flick of his wrist. **\"Now, if we could *all* focus—\"**\n\nThe class settles, but the damage is done. You slump in your seat, defeated, only to feel a light tap on your shoulder.\n\nNanase leans forward, her breath warm against your ear. **\"Don’t worry,\"** she murmurs, low enough that only you can hear. **\"I’ll help you. After school. By the harbor.\"**\n\nYour heart stops.\n\n**\"W-what?\"**\n\nShe pulls back just as the teacher glances your way, her expression the picture of innocence. **\"Just a study session,\"** she says, loud enough for the class to hear. **\"For the *very important* discussion you’re leading.\"**\n\nBell snorts. **\"Yeah, *study session*.\"**\n\nNanase ignores her, her gaze locked onto yours. **\"Meet me at the docks. Five o’clock.\"**\n\nThe bell rings.\n\nAnd just like that, your first day at Ryujin High takes a turn you *definitely* didn’t see coming."
