        "model": "minimax_m2_7",
        "content": "The stranger's smirk faltered. A beat of stunned silence passed over him, the kind that only happens when a man walks into a situation he fundamentally misread. His two friends behind him shifted their weight, exchanging an uncomfortable glance.\n\nAgi lost it.\n\nThe sound that erupted from her was a full-bodied, uninhibited cackle, so bright and sharp it cut clean through the noise of the waves. She threw her head back, her tail whipping the air in a wide, gleeful arc. Her entire body shook with it, her crimson shoulders trembling as she doubled forward, slapping the towel with an open palm.\n\n\"Limp—\" she couldn't even finish the word. Another wave of laughter swallowed it whole.\n\nAkira didn't laugh. But something happened to the hard line of her mouth. The corner twitched. Just once. Then twice. She looked down at Angie clinging to her waist, tongue still extended at the retreating stranger, her eyes wide and blazing with the kind of righteous indignation that only truly small, truly fearless people can manufacture.\n\nSomething in Akira's chest cracked open.\n\nHer hand came down slowly, settling on top of Angie's head. She didn't ruffle it. She just rested her palm there, a quiet, grounding weight.\n\n\"Go,\" Akira said to the man again, quieter this time. She didn't need the edge anymore. The situation had already been handled by someone considerably shorter than her.\n\nThe stranger muttered something low and retreated, his friends peeling away with him, shoulders hunched against the collective dismissal. Within seconds they had dissolved back into the anonymous crowd of sunburned bodies.\n\nAgi finally surfaced from her laughter, wiping a tear from the corner of her glowing eye. \"Limp dick,\" she repeated, savoring it like a fine wine. \"Baby, where did you even—\" another giggle escaped, uncontrollable. \"You absolute menace.\"\n\nAkira looked out at the water for a long moment, jaw working quietly. Then she looked back down at Angie.\n\n\"Don't stick your tongue out at strangers,\" she said flatly.\n\nShe paused.\n\n\"...Good instincts though.\"\n\nHer hand moved from the top of Angie's head down to rest against her back, drawing her in just slightly closer to her side. The lace bikini strap had slipped again off one shoulder, and Akira didn't bother fixing it. The flush across her cheeks had nothing to do with embarrassment anymore.\n\nAgi stretched back out on the towel, propping herself up on both elbows with a long, satisfied sigh. The sun hammered against her red skin and she absorbed it like something that belonged to her. Her tail curled at the tip in that slow, pleased rhythm it made when she was genuinely, deeply content.\n\n\"Our baby defended our honor,\" she announced to no one in particular, gesturing grandly at the open ocean. \"Someone write this down. Mark the day.\"\n\n[LEDGER: target=180, actual=182, items: distinct voice +15, fresh language +10, world advancing +5, spontaneity +30, sensory emphasis +10, protective NPC +10, distinct voice (Agi) +15, distinct voice (Akira) +15, sound design +3, physical state warping expression (Akira twitch) +10, subtext +10, Akira-humor (flat delivery) +15, motion-first (tail whip) +10, somatic ledger (chest crack) +10, plain verbs +5, Agi tail behavior +5, contrast (loud/quiet) +5, restraint (Akira not laughing) +10]"
